value.0: I have nothing for you right now.

It is said that all Garou were Silver Fangs in the beginning. If one were to take the single best quality from each of the tribes and bring them together in a single  Garou, that Garou would be a Silver Fang. While many would contest this, none can deny that the Silver Fangs, more so than any other tribe, have been the rallying point, and leaders of last resort for the Garou race. The palpable charisma and confidence we exude has made us obvious leaders among Garou.

We are noble Garou are known for our physical beauty, courage, wisdom, and honor. We tend to be very socially apt and a employ a wide variety of skills and gifts. The noble history of the tribe lays a heavy burden on our shoulders. Still, those who mock our tribe never do so to our faces.

In someways. But it is our sacred duty to meditate, not slaughter. But when our ire is raised, however, the we will shed blood as eagerly as the Fenrir. A Silver Fangs has to lead by example. By exemplifying the most noble of Garou traits - wisdom, courage, and honor - We inspire those around us to act likewise. The Silver Fang history is filled with heroism. Remember that pup.

Many tribes feel it is fair to label us, Silver Fangs snobbish. But we view our leadership in Garou society as a service our ancestors have charged us to uphold. Our nobility is as much if not more an honor than a birthright.   We are fiercely loyal to each other, the Silver Fang view themselves very much as a venerable household, bearers of centuries of tradition among Garou society. Although learning how to be an effective leader is an expectation among us. We are quick to aid and support one another without hesitation. The occasions when a Silver Fang must choose between loyalty to their tribe versus to their pack can become the source of longtime feuds between Garou. Such rifts, are rarely displayed in public however, since the discord sown often does more harm than good.

Be sure you do. Often we are the first to organize efforts against the Wyrm, trying to make best use of resources and public momentum, often appealing to the Garou sense of immediate action. Even in situations where rushing in is clearly undesirable, we tend to get the ball rolling as soon as possible. And if our plans needs to be held back a bit, we will be in a better position to put the brakes on if we are the acknowledged leaders of the efforts.
Which clan would you like to know the view of?

They are...a different breed among us. Their traditions are based upon entirely different values. One wonders what keeps them fighting for Gaia when the Weaver's temptations seem so prevalent in them.

Garou have so little in common with the Silver Fangs as the Silent Striders. Nomads, rootless, and serving no ancestors, they are the paradox among wolves and men. Do not expect their fealty to the Sept.

Shameful and backstabbing, these Garou have lost sight of their honor. Though they have method and usually have Gaia's interests at heart, their dalliance with Wyrm things puts them in a position to be tempted. However, none understand the enemy so well as they.
Difficult to govern, but their motives are well understood. Give them the territory they seek and they will respect yours.

The sword of Gaia. When their honor does not dictate otherwise, these Garou respect the chain of command better than most. When they choose to break ranks, there is little to convince them otherwise. Though they should not be treated as a tool, well-directed, they are among the most effective battle resources.

A fine example of a rich heritage that is well-appreciated. There is more to the Fianna than their families, however. They understand more at times about how the Umbra works than they do about the mundane world.
Every leadership needs diplomacy, at which the Children of Gaia seem to excel.
Of all Garou the Bone Gnawers show the least respect for the noble traditions of our collective ancestry. But amongst themselves, they are very loyal. A paradox, to be sure.
One of the many splintered viewpoints among the tribes. At least their separatist attitude stops at gender.
So that means we are the best?
So we are the superiority of the Garou?
I will remember it.
I shall strive to become a great leader then.
What is our views on the other tribes then?
